  "title": "Service Technician (VEP)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Responding to and resolving fault calls referred by other technicians.</li><li>Performing basic checks and troubleshooting on PC systems and power generators.</li><li>Liaising with relevant authorities (like NCS and LTA in Singapore) regarding application and network issues for the VEP system.</li><li>Troubleshooting CEPAS readers and conducting monthly power generator checks.</li><li>Arranging the deployment of other technicians and managing liaison with LTA representatives regarding project faults. .</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Min Nitec and  above</li><li>Min 1 year of working experience </li></ul><p>To submit your application, please apply online to <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong></a>or call <strong>+(65) </strong><a href=\"tel:6513 5697\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p><p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p><p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br /><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
